The course allows to acquire the basic knowledge of the legislative acts regulating the organization of education and the skills  in the interpretation and application of the legislation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To support the development of a student as a teacher or head of educational institution who has an overview of education legislation and is aware of the rights and obligations arising from legislation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject: 1)	knows the hierarchy, structure and drafting process of legislation; 2)	is familiar with the legislation regulating education and employment in an educational institution; 3)	is able to find in the legislative acts provisions regulating the organization of studies and the rights and obligations of the parties involved in the educational institution; 4)	is able to find solutions to various cases of study organization based on legislative acts 5)	is able to find solutions to cases involving different parties` rights and obligations, based on legislative acts.
